          <text><![CDATA[<b><br /> </b><b>No Guns for Terrorists Act of 2018</b><br /><br />This bill amends the federal criminal code to make it a crime to knowingly sell or transfer a firearm to a known or suspected terrorist, as determined by the Department of Justice. (The Federal Bureau of Investigation administers the Terrorist Screening Center, which maintains the Terrorist Screening Database&#8212;the U.S. government's consolidated database of individuals known or reasonably suspected to be involved in terrorist activities.)<br /><br /><br />]]></text>
